    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "Command, Stewart Air Field, Newburgh, New York). He called back and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "said their only instructions was to keep fighters on Alert Status.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "Told him we could have both off the ground in 4 (four) minutes.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "\"Targets were appearing with some regularity and proceeding",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "South.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "\"They all traveled at a speed of between 100 and 125 miles",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "per hour. Fading and reappearing at various intervals. All but",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "one originated in the area. One did appear at 10 miles North of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "Clinton and faded right at the area line. Reappearance of this",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "target or at least one on the same course 180 degrees was 8 (eight)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "miles inside area. This target faded after three sweeps (Revolutions",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "of the indicator on the Radar Scope which makes four revolutions per",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "minute).",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "\"The tracks varied at time from one applicable to very light",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "A/C (aircraft) up to A/C of the C-47 variety (Meaning the reflected",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "intensity of Radar waves made the target appear at first like a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "small aircraft and then like a large one).",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "\"We operated both on High and Low Beam and picked up the same",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "tracks.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "\"All traveled at the same approximate speed and general",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "course. During the night this course spread from 170 degrees to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "230 degrees (magnetic compass heading).",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
